        "title": "Lasted two uses. (Update, replaced under warranty)",
        "link": "https://www.amazon.com/gp/customer-reviews/R1QHPEM3EM80A1/ref=cm_cr_dp_d_rvw_ttl?ie=UTF8",
        "text": "I like the idea and everything about the swamp cooler, except that it fell apart the second time my dog wore it. As shown in the photos above, the buckle pulled out from the vest. The buckle stayed latched--the end sewn into the bottom of the vest pulled out. I am not sure, but it looks like it was not sewn in correctly. Hopefully I can get a replacement for free and then we'll update the review if the new one lasts longer. **UPDATE: kudos to Amazon and the seller NetRush. NetRush reached out to me to make things right, and Amazon has already accepted my return. I have my second one and will update with its durability.",
        "rating": 4,
        "date": "Reviewed in the United States on May 7, 2024",
        "extracted_date": "2024-05-07",
        "profile": {
          "id": "AHRR37WTYUXSHDMCHWV3QT5RFNFA",
